ğŸ§  Class in PHP

A class is a blueprint for creating objects

It defines properties (variables) and methods (functions)

Used in Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)

Helps in code reusability

Improves program structure

Supports encapsulation and abstraction

Created using the class keyword


-------

ğŸ§© Object in PHP

An object is an instance of a class

It is used to access properties and methods of a class

Objects represent real-world entities

Created using the new keyword

Each object has its own data

Objects help in implementing OOP concepts

Used to call class functions

----
ğŸ”’ Encapsulation in PHP

Encapsulation means binding data and methods into a single unit (class)

It is used to hide internal details of the class

Data is protected using access modifiers

Access modifiers are private, protected, public

Prevents direct access to variables

Data can be accessed using getter and setter methods

Improves security and data integrity

-------

ğŸ§¬ Inheritance in PHP

Inheritance allows one class to use properties and methods of another class

The main class is called the parent (base) class

The new class is called the child (derived) class

It promotes code reusability

Avoids duplication of code

Implemented using the extends keyword

Child class can add its own features

-----

Types of Inheritance in PHP

Single Inheritance â€“ One child class inherits one parent class

Multilevel Inheritance â€“ A class inherits from a child class (grandparent â†’ parent â†’ child)

Hierarchical Inheritance â€“ Multiple child classes inherit from one parent

Multiple Inheritance â€“ Not supported directly in PHP (done using interfaces/traits)

Inheritance is implemented using the extends keyword

Helps in code reusability

Reduces code duplication

----

ğŸ­ Abstraction in PHP

Abstraction means hiding implementation details and showing only essential features

It focuses on what to do, not how it works

Achieved using abstract classes or interfaces

Abstract class can have both abstract and normal methods

Abstract methods must be implemented in child class

Cannot create object of an abstract class

Improves security and reduces complexity

