ğŸ”„ Polymorphism in PHP

Polymorphism means one method, different behavior

Same function name can work in different ways

Achieved through method overriding

Happens when child class redefines parent method

Supports flexibility in programs

Reduces code complexity

Helps in implementing dynamic behavior
--------

ğŸ§  OOP (Object-Oriented Programming) in PHP

OOP is a programming method based on classes and objects

It helps organize code in a structured way

Improves code reusability

Makes programs easier to maintain

Focuses on real-world entities

Supports data security

Reduces code duplication

Used in large web applications

---------

ğŸ§© Traits in PHP

Traits are used to reuse code in multiple classes

They solve the problem of multiple inheritance in PHP

A trait can contain methods and properties

Defined using the trait keyword

Included in a class using the use keyword

Helps avoid code duplication

Improves code modularity
---------

âœ¨ Magic Methods in PHP

Magic methods are special predefined functions in PHP

Their names start with double underscores __

They are automatically called when certain actions happen

Used in Object-Oriented Programming

Help control object behavior

Used for constructor, destructor, overloading, etc.

Improve flexibility of classes


-------

ğŸ— Constructor in PHP (__construct)

A constructor is a special method in a class

It runs automatically when an object is created

Used to initialize class properties

Helps set default values

Its name is __construct()

Can accept parameters

Improves object setup process

----

.

ğŸ’¥ Destructor in PHP (__destruct)

A destructor is a special method in a class

It runs automatically when an object is destroyed

Used to perform cleanup tasks

Helps close database connections

Used to free resources

Its name is __destruct()

Called at the end of script execution

--------

JOIN in SQL

JOIN is used to combine data from two or more tables

Works using a common column (usually primary & foreign key)

Helps fetch related data in one query

Used in database-driven applications

Improves data retrieval

Essential in relational databases


